The paper proposes a method for imitation learning of a control policy represented by parametrized hierarchical procedures (PHP), which is a program-like structure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of hierarchical control policies and the focus on improving data efficiency and generalization suggest that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses observation-action traces and may involve image processing, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
